			<div class="content" id="post-content-3570173">
									

<p>I get that Prometheus Labs was significantly ahead of conventional technology. What I don't get is why it was ever classified as *anomalous*&#8212;was the Foundation incapable of building more and later found out it was because the notes were incomplete or damaged in some fashion? Does biological 3D printing go against an established scientific theory that has since been overturned?</p>
<p>If the Foundation's scientists can figure out how it works and explain how it works in a way that doesn't violate any well-established scientific theory, it shouldn't be considered anomalous. And if they can't, the Foundation should intervene and classify Organovo's machine as an SCP.</p>
<p>Alternatively, the Foundation might declare the machine to be a result of an SCP (perhaps Prometheus got their knowledge from sources that were actually anomalous), but we aren't given any information into what led them to arrive at that conclusion.</p>

							</div>

								
					
