<p>Excellent. It's a little simplistic but I think that works to its benefit - whereas you could've got this bogged down in sidestories and intrigue it's a pretty effective proof-of-concept for the human race catching up to the Foundation's rate for reality-fuckery. That's what appeals to me the most about this: the way it catalogs the tech's treatment from inception to standardization feels really tight. The article's short, and some of the end bits feel a little disconnected from the overall experience - in particular, tying the achievement to one specific fictional mega/corp felt a little disingenuous, though that was offset by the way you included various other institutions, and as a whole I really liked it.</p>

