<p>I don't know enough about bioprinting to evaluate this from an actual-science standpoint, but I dig the idea of the foundation containing things because they don't understand them, and realizing later on that they got carried away. This is a +1 for me.</p>
<p>It fits well into my personal canon for the foundation as a whole. They make mistakes like this for the very same reason they're able to amass world-controlling levels of power without fragmenting into smaller groups: because they're so agonizingly <em>thorough</em> about what they're doing that they stick to their goal regardless of context. Any person or group acting on that kind of rigidity is going to have screwups like this along the way, and seeing them have to correct it really fleshes the universe out for me.</p>

